<item>
            <title>[LU-17958] Clients can&apos;t mount after server upgrade</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17958</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After we upgrade servers to 2.15.5RC2, clients were in RC1 can&apos;t mount with following order:&lt;br/&gt;
mount -t lustre 172.16.5.5@tcp,172.16.5.6@tcp:172.16.5.7@tcp,172.16.5.8@tcp:172.16.5.3@tcp,172.16.5.4@tcp:172.16.5.1@tcp,172.16.5.2@tcp:/testfs /lustre/testfs/client&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, this order worked&lt;br/&gt;
mount -t lustre 172.16.5.1@tcp,172.16.5.2@tcp:172.16.5.3@tcp,172.16.5.4@tcp:172.16.5.5@tcp,172.16.5.6@tcp:172.16.5.7@tcp,172.16.5.8@tcp:/testfs /lustre/testfs/client&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;for the clients that update to RC2, mount worked with both order&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
